  "further_info": "Recommended Reading The following four papers constitute the material for the midterm exam. [1] Aguilar-Gomez, Sandra, Holt Dwyer, Joshua Graff Zivin, Matthew Neidell (2022) This Is Air: The “Nonhealth” Effects of Air Pollution. Annual Review of Resource Economics 2022 14:1, 403-425 [2] Aldy, J. E., Auffhammer, M., Cropper, M., Fraas, A., & Morgenstern, R. (2022). Looking back at 50 years of the Clean Air Act. Journal of Economic Literature, 60(1), 179-232. [3] Brewer, D., Dench, D., & Taylor, L. O. (2023). Advances in causal inference at the intersection of air pollution and health outcomes. Annual Review of Resource Economics, 15(1), 455-469. [4] Mejino-Lopez, J. & Oliu-Barton, M. (2024). How much does Europe pay for clean air? Bruegel Working Paper 15/2024.",
